04/05/2011
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Three Bulgarian citizens are accused of providing financial support to terrorist activities, media reported on Tuesday (May 3rd). 
The three are part of a group of nine people arrested in April during an operation against the radical organisation Jamaat Shariat, which comes from Northern Caucasus. 
Media in Bulgaria reported that the three Bulgarian citizens who were arrested are of Turkish origin. 
They were allegedly involved in producing fake documents for members of the terror group. 
(Darik, Focus, Dnevnik, Trud, Novinar - 03/05/11)
